document_data.Quotes:
Here are a few excerpts from the book:

{{Quote|''"Castles are well and good...but if you've not the strength to hold them...they rapidly become grand expensive tombs"''}}

{{Quote|''"Death walks behind each of us, every day...none can outrun his fate, though many try strange and elaborate ways of doing so."''}}

{{Quote|''"One man's doom is another's dream. Both are all about us, every day...Even the gods have their dooms."''}}
